Build only the libcxi shared library (libcxi.so) plus its public header and
pkg-config file -- the pieces libfabric's `cxi` provider link-depends on.

Upstream Makefile.am also builds the utils/ diagnostic tools, a criterion test
suite and the retry_handler systemd service. Those pull in fuse / libyaml /
lm-sensors and compile GPU sources against the host's /opt/rocm. 
This trims Makefile.am down to src/libcxi.la and removes the now-unused LIBFUSE 
/ LIBYAML / sensors.h probes from configure.ac. The `git describe` version stamp 
is dropped too: its only consumer was the retry_handler, which this patch removes.

Author: Aayush Joglekar <aayush.joglekar@surf.nl>

